From: Qiang Yu <Qiang.Yu@amd.com>
Date: Fri, 17 Mar 2017 18:18:14 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 0167/1453] drm/amdgpu: [hybrid] disable DC when virtual
 display is enabled

Host OS can also enable virtual display when needed.

Change-Id: I28375f2637c56ce42439c3026f495f987fc134d1
Signed-off-by: Qiang Yu <Qiang.Yu@amd.com>
Reviewed-by: Junwei Zhang <Jerry.Zhang@amd.com>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_device.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_device.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_device.c
index 93f058964622..9cb84aa97dad 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_device.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_device.c
@@ -2540,7 +2540,7 @@ bool amdgpu_device_asic_has_dc_support(enum amd_asic_type asic_type)
  */
 bool amdgpu_device_has_dc_support(struct amdgpu_device *adev)
 {
-	if (amdgpu_sriov_vf(adev))
+	if (adev->enable_virtual_display)
 		return false;
 
 	return amdgpu_device_asic_has_dc_support(adev->asic_type);
